document_data.History:
Prior to {{yearlink|976}}, Gruanthe had become the leader of a splinter faction of mages and clerics from Estagund, most importantly from the faiths of [[Sharess]] and [[Lliira]], whom he promised to lead into a new place, where they could worship freely, without concern for the laws of Estagund.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|164}} Before that he had once been a rival of [[Umbeso]] in seeking positions of power,{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|177}}

On {{yearlink|976}}, while in Lliiress, Gruanthe came up with the scheme to request the aid of the blue dragon Gerinvioch. He summoned an imp to scout out the lair,{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|166-169}}

Gruanthe sent a team of twenty to acquire the artifact; twelve of them died in the process, with four more dying on the way back.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|170-171}} He then sent word to the dragon, who arrived and began a ritual; the human tried to smooth over the doubts of those who were still unsure about the dragon's spell.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|172-173}}

After the dragon completed his spell, and the town discovered alongside Gruanthe that they were trapped and that spells would kill them, Gruanthe's mood and stability began to slip from frustration.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|174-178}} He died shortly after, when the temptation to scry on Gerinvioch became too great.
